SIMPLE: endanger
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Endanger
<hw>En*dan"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Endangered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Endangering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To put
to hazard; to bring into danger or peril; to expose to loss or injury;
<as>as, to <ex>endanger</ex> life or peace</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the other difficulties of his reign only exercised without
<qex>endangering</qex> him.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To incur the hazard of; to risk.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that turneth the humors back . . . <qex>endangereth</qex>
malign ulcers.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>endangered</ent>⟦br⟧
